interaction complexes which cannot be mapped to\n1-complexes after removing a small fraction of cells. We define this more\nprecisely below; in a sense this generalizes the idea of an expander graph.\nSurprisingly, such complexes do exist as will be shown elsewhere, and have\nuseful properties in quantum coding theory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Jan 2012 22:36:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Aug 2012 16:25:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 28 Nov 2012 20:41:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-04-16"}
